info.title: Neuroblastoma (NBL) Data Dictionary
info.name: nbl_v3.0
info.description: The NBL data dictionary is a balloted data standard built by an international group of pediatric neuroblastoma experts and maintained by the Pediatric Cancer Data Commons (PCDC) at the University of Chicago in collaboration with the International Neuroblastoma Risk Group (INRG). It is based on the collective experience of its contributors.

table.name: subject_identifier
table.implementation_note: Will be included in every table

table.name: subject_characteristics
table.implementation_note: One row per subject per study

permissible_values.value: Subject is censored (i.e. has had no events(s))
Subject has had one or more events

variables.name: AGE_AT_CENSOR_STATUS
variables.description: The subject's age (in days) at the time of censor status recording.

table.name: disease_phase_timing
table.implementation_note: One row per subject per disease phase

variables.name: DISEASE_PHASE
implementation_note: Disease phase could be "Initial Diagnosis" phase, or a "Relapse" phase, etc...

variables.name: DISEASE_PHASE_NUMBER
implementation_note: Ordinal number of the disease phase, grouped within subcategory. I.e. number Relapse 1, 2, 3, 4, etc... and Progression 1, 2, 3, 4, etc...

variables.name: AGE_AT_DISEASE_PHASE
variables.description: Age in Days at Disease Phase
implementation_note: Disease phase could be the "Initial Diagnosis" phase, or a "Relapse" phase, etc...

variables.name: YEAR_AT_DISEASE_PHASE
implementation_note: Disease phase could be the "Initial Diagnosis" phase, or a "Relapse" phase, etc...

permissible_values.value: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander
mapping: skos:exactMatch [nbl_v2.0].[RACE].[5=Native Hawaiian or other Pacific Islander]

table.name: survival_characteristics
table.implementation_note: One row per subject per cause of death, per treatment type, per cause of death detail

variables.name: AGE_AT_LKSS
variables.description: Age in Days at Last Known Survival Status

variables.name: DISEASE_PHASE
implementation_note: Only fill in Disease phase, Disease phase number, Course, and Course number if "AGE_" not known
Disease phase could be "Initial Diagnosis" phase, or a "Relapse" phase, etc...

variables.name: DISEASE_PHASE_NUMBER
implementation_note: Only fill in Disease phase, Disease phase number, Course, and Course number if "AGE_" not known
Ordinal number of the disease phase, grouped within subcategory. I.e. number Relapse 1, 2, 3, 4, etc... and Progression 1, 2, 3, 4, etc...

table.name: disease_characteristics
table.implementation_note: One row per subject per disease characteristic

variables.name: INITIAL_TREATMENT_CATEGORY
variables.description: The category of initial treatment that the patient receive for their disease.

permissible_values.value: Intensive multi-modality therapy: specific type unknown
mapping: skos:exactMatch [nbl_v2.0].[INIT_TREAT].[3=Intensive multi-modality therapy: specific type unknown]

permissible_values.value: Intensive multi-modality therapy: no stem cell or bone marrow transplant
mapping: skos:exactMatch [nbl_v2.0].[INIT_TREAT].[4=Intensive multi-modality therapy: no stem cell or bone marrow transplant]

permissible_values.value: Intensive multi-modality therapy: plus stem cell or bone marrow transplant
mapping: skos:exactMatch [nbl_v2.0].[INIT_TREAT].[5=Intensive multi-modality therapy: plus stem cell or bone marrow transplant]

permissible_values.value: Intensive multi-modality therapy: plus stem cell or bone marrow transplant and anti-GD2 antibody
mapping: skos:exactMatch [nbl_v2.0].[INIT_TREAT].[6=Intensive multi-modality therapy: plus stem cell or bone marrow transplant and anti-GD2 antibody]

table.name: tumor_assessment
table.implementation_note: One row per subject per tumor assessment per tumor site

variables.name: AGE_AT_TUMOR_ASSESSMENT
variables.description: Age in Days at Tumor Assessment

variables.name: TUMOR_STATE
variables.description: A condition or state of a tumor at a particular time and a particular tumor site.

variables.name: TUMOR_SITE
implementation_note: If there were multiple primary sites, include one observation per primary site.

table.name: staging

variables.name: AGE_AT_STAGING
variables.description: Age in Days of Staging Assessment

variables.name: STAGE_SYSTEM

table.name: histology
table.implementation_note: One row per subject per histologic assessment

variables.name: STAGE
implementation_note: Tied to stage system.

variables.name: AGE_AT_HIST_ASSESSMENT
variables.description: Age in Days of Histology Assessment

variables.name: DISEASE_PHASE
implementation_note: Only fill in Disease phase, Disease phase number, Course, and Course number if "AGE_" not known
Disease phase could be "Initial Diagnosis" phase, or a "Relapse" phase, etc...

variables.name: DISEASE_PHASE_NUMBER

variables.name: HISTOLOGY

mapping: skos:exactMatch [nbl_v2.0].[DIAG].[3=Ganglioneuroma (Schwannian stroma-dominant), maturing subtype OR Ganglioneuroblastoma, well differentiated (Schwannian stroma-rich)]

implementation_note: If multiple histological findings, include one observation per histological finding.

variables.name: HISTOLOGY_GRADE
implementation_note: For GCT, this is only associated with Mature Teratoma.

implementation_note: Only fill in Disease phase, Disease phase number, Course, and Course number if "AGE_" not known
Ordinal number of the disease phase, grouped within subcategory. I.e. number Relapse 1, 2, 3, 4, etc... and Progression 1, 2, 3, 4, etc...

variables.name: DNA_INDEX
implementation_note: If multiple statuses apply, include one observation per status.

implementation_note: If multiple molecular abnormalities, include one observation per molecular abnormality.

mapping: skos:narrowMatch [nbl_v2.0].[MYCN].[0=Not amplified (≤ 4 times of the reference on chromosome 2q)]
skos:narrowMatch [nbl_v2.0].[MYCN].[1=Amplified (> 4 times of the reference on chromosome 2q)]
